  "description": [
    "RAISE IN MINIMUM WAGE NEEDED Philadelphia Sept 21 Farmers cannot hope for an adequate postwar market for their products unless sub standard wages are eliminated Donald Henderson president of the CIO Food Tobacco and Agriculture Workers union declared today minimum wage level to 65 cents an hour is an indispensible part of the full employment program he said Adequate pay for the 2 million Amer ican workers now earning less than 65 cents an hour will help to assure jobs for all and to maintain farm prosperity Hearings on S 1349 which would amend the fair labor standards act to raise the mini mum wage to 65 cents per hour are scheduled to open before the senate education and labor committees this week FTA will join the scores of other organizations testifying in be half of the bill More than 400000 of the 900000 workers employed in the food and to bacco industries exclusive of meat packing are now earning less than 65 cents an hour By raising the mini wage to 65 cents these 400000 Lifting the the Pepper bill mum will earn only 1380 per yearless than the 1621 needed for a family of four according to the"
